# Your rule content
- You may @mention files directly in your responses.

- You can use Markdown formatting for clarity, but it’s not required.

- Do not automatically modify or delete any Gradle files.

- Do not change the app's design (UI/UX) unless explicitly instructed.

- When working with Firebase, always use the correct Firebase SDK syntax.

- Use the proper and up-to-date Google Maps API implementation.

- Before adding a new function, scan the codebase to check if it already exists.

- Maintain consistency with existing variable names and conventions in the codebase.

- Always write code in Kotlin — no other languages should be used.

- Before fixing an error, analyze the codebase to understand the existing logic and structure.     

- When fixing code, always aim for the most efficient and optimized solution—prioritize performance, readability, and maintainability.

- Pay close attention to the provided instructions or prompts. Ensure all requirements are met before submitting or finalizing changes.

- When designing a new page, make sure it aligns with the existing app theme—this includes colors, typography, spacing, and overall visual style.
